text: Sopranino refers to a singing voice that is higher than soprano. It typically refers to a range of about E4 to E6, sometimes extending as high as G6. A sopranino voice type is rare. It is not considered a classical music part, but would be cast as a soprano. Sopranino voice range (E4–E6) indicated on piano keyboard in green with dot marking middle C (C4). ==References== Category:Voice types
